                "child_table": "",
                "description": "You must complete 96 credit points comprising all the requirements from Parts A and B as described in the Bachelor of Arts degree. <br /> At least 24 credit points must be completed at Level 3. <br /><br />For Part B Arts Specified Study, you must complete 12 credit points of units from the Professional Futures domains and the remaining 12 credit points should be selected from Level 1, 2 or 3 Arts' elective units. <br /><br />For your discipline studies in the double degree secondary education specialisation, you must complete a Victorian Institute of Teaching minor study in one secondary teaching area. The minor study must consist of four units, with no more than two units at first year level. Space for the minor study units will come from elective unit allocations on the course map. Approved disciplines can be found on the secondary specialist areas page: https://www.monash.edu/education/students/courses/units/secondary-specialisms",
